SIMPLE: hoary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoary
<hw>Hoar"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>White or
whitish.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>hoary</xex> willows.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>White or gray with age; hoar; <as>as, <ex>hoary</ex>
hairs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Reverence the <qex>hoary</qex> head.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. T.
Dwight.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> Hence, <def>remote in time past; <as>as, <ex>hoary</ex>
antiquity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Moldy; mossy; musty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of a pale silvery gray.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with short, dense, grayish
white hairs; canescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hoary bat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>an American
bat (<spn>Atalapha cinerea</spn>), having the hair yellowish, or brown,
tipped with white.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoatzin</ent>⟦br⟧
